<font color="#FF0000">AO AND THINGS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep 18 19:47:36 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art , I was up in the Central Highlands.  Started out in Ft. Lewis,Wa. as part of the 4th Inf.  ..  Got on a boat, landed in Qui Nhon, 10-65, headed up the pass and got roped into the 1st. Cav. in An Khe.  The rest of the group went on up into Pleiku.  The 4th Inf. that is.  Stayed with the Cav. until Jan. of 67 and got shipped up to Chu Lai where the Americal Div. was forming up.  When I shipped out in May of 67 I had to return to An Khe to cycle out.<br>
Cookie, we didn't do a lot of H&amp;I or Illum. Those 8 inchers would put up a flare that would burn all nite!  Youse, squids, hated to call in those rounds because bursting radius was said to be 1000 meters.  Besides, there is nothing more awesome than three batteries doing a fire mission at once.  TOT.  Well, all right, there was the Dragon ships.. Those were pretty, too!
